Hiro.

198
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:18,791
Hiro!

199
00:21:24,958 --> 00:21:26,083
Saeko!

200
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:36,041
-Hiro!
-Hey.

201
00:21:38,875 --> 00:21:39,916
Don't trip.

202
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:45,833
Welcome back.

203
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:47,250
I've been waiting.

204
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:51,291
I heard you're concerned about work.

205
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:52,833
So, what happened?

206
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:55,625
-You can tell me anything.
-Well…

207
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,291
It's nothing.

208
00:21:59,541 --> 00:22:01,833
Everything's going well. Nothing's wrong.

209
00:22:03,125 --> 00:22:03,958
What?

210
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,708
I found out about Yusuke.

211
00:22:17,125 --> 00:22:18,333
It's a sad thing.

212
00:22:21,333 --> 00:22:22,708
So I wanted to see you.

213
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:27,500
I thought coming to Hawaii
would do you good.

214
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:32,666
These plains…

215
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:36,916
The wind and sky… will surely

216
00:22:38,250 --> 00:22:40,791
give you strength and good fortune.

217
00:22:41,625 --> 00:22:42,916
That's how I felt.

218
00:22:45,541 --> 00:22:46,375
Yeah.

219
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:51,500
When I spoke with my wife at her grave,

220
00:22:52,291 --> 00:22:54,000
she said to call you over.

221
00:22:54,083 --> 00:22:57,583
But it's not that easy,
since you have work and all.

222
00:22:58,208 --> 00:22:59,458
And it's not cheap.

223
00:23:01,791 --> 00:23:02,625
That's why…

224
00:23:05,375 --> 00:23:11,708
I lied and told them
I wanted to talk to you about work.

225
00:23:12,583 --> 00:23:13,708
What?

226
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:17,625
You got here on the company's dime, right?

227
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:19,166
All right.

228
00:23:20,666 --> 00:23:21,791
For real?

229
00:23:23,458 --> 00:23:25,291
Come on, Hiro.

230
00:23:27,916 --> 00:23:29,416
All right then.

231
00:23:30,416 --> 00:23:31,375
Let's get going.

232
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:39,000
We have a proposal for you.

233
