Want me to tell you
what you need most right now?

257
00:28:33,666 --> 00:28:34,500
Huh?

258
00:28:40,166 --> 00:28:42,125
So, what's your name?

259
00:28:44,458 --> 00:28:45,708
My name…

260
00:28:47,541 --> 00:28:48,416
Hypothetically,

261
00:28:49,666 --> 00:28:51,583
let's say it's Saeko for now.

262
00:28:52,458 --> 00:28:54,458
My name is Yusuke.

263
00:28:54,541 --> 00:28:57,416
That's not hypothetical.
It's really Yusuke.

264
00:29:01,791 --> 00:29:05,541
You're probably upset over
something bad or sad that happened.

265
00:29:06,041 --> 00:29:08,791
So, why not have some coffee
and settle down first?

266
00:29:08,875 --> 00:29:11,625
Drinking coffee might not fix the problem,

267
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:13,083
but taking a breather

268
00:29:13,166 --> 00:29:16,500
can make your situation
seem a little less overbearing.

269
00:29:16,583 --> 00:29:18,708
You'll think, "It's okay. It'll work out."

270
00:29:19,208 --> 00:29:23,250
It can also help you see new things
or find beauty you didn't notice before.

271
00:29:23,333 --> 00:29:27,541
Coffee has that kind of power.
Did you know that?

272
00:29:30,625 --> 00:29:32,625
What you need right now

273
00:29:34,208 --> 00:29:36,750
is probably… coffee.

274
00:29:40,541 --> 00:29:41,666
So, what's your dream?

275
00:29:43,416 --> 00:29:44,250
My dream?

276
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:48,041
You want to know my dream all of a sudden?

277
00:29:54,625 --> 00:29:57,750
To live a cool life
and become happier than anyone.

278
00:29:58,333 --> 00:30:00,375
To live a fulfilling life with good taste.

279
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:04,541
To actually contribute
to society through my work.

280
00:30:05,916 --> 00:30:06,833
And…

281
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:11,500
to find a man who'll fall
head over heels in love with me.

282
00:30:12,916 --> 00:30:13,875
I could go on.

283
00:30:15,041 --> 00:30:16,166
But what about you?

284
00:30:17,875 --> 00:30:20,458
My dream is to be a softener.

285
00:30:22,708 --> 00:30:23,541
What's that mean?

286
00:30:23,625 --> 00:30:26,958
Well, softeners are a necessity,
aren't they?

287
00:30:27,041 --> 00:30:29,375
Without them, the world feels all coarse.

288
00:30:34,333 --> 00:30:35,875
It's the same with coffee.

289
00:30:36,958 --> 00:30:38,916
It's kind of a softener too.

290
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:39,833
What?

291
00:31:06,625 --> 00:31:08,500
Thank you for the coffee.

292
00:31:20,416 --> 00:31:21,291
What do you want?

293
00:31:22,333 --> 00:31:23,458
I thought you left.

294
00:31:24,750 --> 00:31:26,708
I didn't finish what I came to say.

295
00:31:27,208 --> 00:31:29,208
Please hear me out until the end.

296
00:31:30,166 --> 00:31:31,583
Forget about the contract.

297
00:31:31,666 --> 00:31:34,166
Just listen to my story, please.

298
00:31:38,958 --> 00:31:40,958
The work at my last company

299
00:31:41,041 --> 00:31:44,583
was so hard that it broke me
mentally and physically.

300
00:31:44,666 --> 00:31:48,083
I couldn't take it,
so I quit and went on a solo trip.

301
00:31:49,458 --> 00:31:50,291
To this island.

302
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:53,958
I was fed up with everything.

303
00:31:55,625 --> 00:31:57,625
What saved me then

304
00:31:58,125 --> 00:32:02,083
was the cup of coffee
I had at a small café.

305
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,291
It was so good,

306
00:32:04,375 --> 00:32:07,541
I couldn't believe
something that tasty existed.

307
00:32:08,125 --> 00:32:10,375
It was so good, it even made me laugh.

308
00:32:11,041 --> 00:32:14,708
That's when I decided
I wanted to keep living.

309
00:32:15,208 --> 00:32:19,375
The barista there told me
that the coffee came from this farm.

310
00:32:21,458 --> 00:32:22,916
Then, I went back to Japan

311
00:32:23,416 --> 00:32:25,708
and joined a company
that works with coffee.

312
00:32:26,666 --> 00:32:31,791
I thought I could help people
going through tough or trying times.

313
00:32:33,208 --> 00:32:36,500
Since then, I've wanted to
thank you properly one day,

314
00:32:36,583 --> 00:32:39,500
and I knew your coffee
could find even greater recognition.

315
00:32:41,416 --> 00:32:42,541
That's why I'm here.

316
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:45,250
I wanted to be of help.

317
00:32:45,833 --> 00:32:50,250
But I'm not in it for the money either,
so I'll stop talking about business.

318
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:54,791
For now, let's just
harvest as much as we can.

319
00:32:55,958 --> 00:32:57,208
I'll pick berries too.

320
00:33:00,375 --> 00:33:01,208
What?

321
00:33:02,625 --> 00:33:04,500
Don't be ridiculous.

322
00:33:04,583 --> 00:33:07,458
I don't budge once I've made up my mind.

323
00:33:07,541 --> 00:33:09,750
Sorry, just give up.

324
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:12,333
Fine, then.

325
00:33:14,958 --> 00:33:16,083
And who's that guy?

326
00:33:17,791 --> 00:33:18,708
My thoughts exactly.

327
00:33:20,333 --> 00:33:23,333
Oh, well, I…

328
00:33:25,750 --> 00:33:29,250
I've put my hat in the ring
as a potential suitor.

329
00:33:30,416 --> 00:33:31,250
I see.

330
00:33:32,208 --> 00:33:33,916
I… see.

331
00:33:35,208 --> 00:33:37,708
And so, I'll be helping out too.

332
00:33:38,375 --> 00:33:40,833
I don't have a job right now,
so it's totally fine.

333
00:33:40,916 --> 00:33:41,916
I'll be in your care.

334
00:33:43,041 --> 00:33:44,333
Give me a break.

335
00:33:45,625 --> 00:33:46,750
Give me a break.

336
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:45,916
There we go.

337
00:35:15,875 --> 00:35:17,291
I'll say it again.

338
00:35:21,791 --> 00:35:23,625
Just as I thought, your coffee

339
00:35:25,375 --> 00:35:26,375
is the best.

340
00:35:33,958 --> 00:35:36,583
Well, I think so too.

341
00:35:37,750 --> 00:35:40,125
It's the best in the world.
No doubt about it.

342
00:36:05,583 --> 00:36:07,625
-Whoa!
-Woo-hoo!

343
00:36:07,708 --> 00:36:09,000
This is amazing!

344
00:36:10,083 --> 00:36:11,333
Woo-hoo!

345
00:36:12,041 --> 00:36:13,083
Wow.

346
00:36:14,958 --> 00:36:16,083
You doing okay?

347
00:36:16,166 --> 00:36:17,291
Yeah, I'm good.

348
00:36:17,375 --> 00:36:18,583
Okay.

349
00:36:22,625 --> 00:36:25,041
-Wow.
-Incredible.

350
00:36:25,125 --> 00:36:27,041
-Okay.
-A photo, eh?

351
00:36:27,750 --> 00:36:29,875
-I can't press it.
-Oh, okay. Got it.

352
00:36:31,083 --> 00:36:32,250
-All right. Thanks.
-Sure.

353
00:36:38,291 --> 00:36:40,166
It's so good.
Hey, there's something inside.

354
00:36:44,500 --> 00:36:45,958
Aren't you a bit close?

355
00:36:46,041 --> 00:36:48,500
-You're too slow.
-You're too close.

356
00:36:49,291 --> 00:36:50,750
I can just go for it, right?

357
00:36:50,833 --> 00:36:51,666
Whoa.

358
00:36:51,750 --> 00:36:54,083
Wow, this is nice.

359
00:36:54,166 --> 00:36:55,708
Hey, look at this.

360
00:36:56,416 --> 00:36:57,708
Wait for me.

361
00:36:59,208 --> 00:37:01,125
Whoa. They're swimming!

362
00:37:01,625 --> 00:37:03,833
-You're right.
-Looks refreshing.

363
00:37:03,916 --> 00:37:05,250
I bet it feels good.

364
00:37:05,333 --> 00:37:06,333
Hey. Hold on.

365
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,833
Don't do anything crazy.

366
00:37:09,333 --> 00:37:10,875
You scared me.

367
00:37:11,625 --> 00:37:18,208
But you know, I'm going to keep my name,
my age, and where I Iive a secret.

368
00:37:19,625 --> 00:37:20,458
And I won't ask.

369
00:37:21,416 --> 00:37:22,250
So…

370
00:37:23,375 --> 00:37:25,208
I'm simply "Saeko."

371
00:37:26,375 --> 00:37:27,208
Why?

372
00:37:27,708 --> 00:37:33,000
I mean, we met when I was at a low point.
And it was abroad, to boot.

373
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:37,625
I know it sounds like fate and all,

374
00:37:37,708 --> 00:37:39,250
but I hate stuff like that.

375
00:37:39,750 --> 00:37:41,791
I don't want to get caught up in things,

376
00:37:41,875 --> 00:37:46,958
so let's just have fun in the moment
while we're on this vacation.

377
00:37:47,041 --> 00:37:48,041
Got it?

378
00:37:49,083 --> 00:37:49,916
Got it.

379
00:37:55,625 --> 00:37:57,291
-I'm fine.
-You're walking like this.

380
00:37:59,208 --> 00:38:00,083
Drunk Saeko.

381
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,541
-Now then…
-I'm totally normal.

382
00:38:05,250 --> 00:38:07,500
Come on.

383
00:38:11,416 --> 00:38:12,333
You're so slow.

384
00:38:12,416 --> 00:38:13,666
Wow, I'm beat.

385
00:38:19,041 --> 00:38:20,000
Good night.

386
00:38:21,166 --> 00:38:22,000
Good night.

387
00:38:25,208 --> 00:38:26,458
Good night.

388
00:38:29,583 --> 00:38:30,833
Good night.

389
00:38:37,750 --> 00:38:38,916
-Which room?
-Which room?

390
00:38:49,166 --> 00:38:50,000
Yours?

391
00:39:05,541 --> 00:39:06,375
You're right.

392
00:39:09,458 --> 00:39:10,958
You are a softener.

393
00:39:13,875 --> 00:39:15,708
You want to cuddle me?

394
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:20,375
I do now.

395
00:39:46,875 --> 00:39:49,125
I'm positive we'll meet again someday.

396
00:39:50,333 --> 00:39:51,166
Why's that?

397
00:39:52,541 --> 00:39:58,750
Well, even if you get further
and further away from my sight,

398
00:40:00,125 --> 00:40:03,708
you'll always make your way back to me.

399
00:40:05,166 --> 00:40:06,166
After all,

400
00:40:07,708 --> 00:40:08,875
the world is round.

401
00:40:11,125 --> 00:40:12,000
Are you for real?

402
00:40:14,291 --> 00:40:17,833
When we meet again somewhere,
then it'll be fate.

403
00:40:17,916 --> 00:40:20,041
You have to give up and be my girlfriend.

404
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:21,666
Promise me.

405
00:40:23,333 --> 00:40:26,083
Sure, I'll be your girlfriend.

406
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:28,333
I promise.

407
00:40:59,333 --> 00:41:01,375
Excuse me. Where is the owner?

408
00:41:01,458 --> 00:41:02,666
Oh, he's inside.

409
00:41:02,750 --> 00:41:03,625
Thank you.

410
00:41:11,083 --> 00:41:12,416
Excuse me.

411
00:41:13,416 --> 00:41:16,375
I'm Sugawara from Akane Inc.

412
00:41:17,333 --> 00:41:20,250
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you. I'm Sugawara.

413
00:41:20,750 --> 00:41:23,375
You asked to do
a coffee collaboration with us, right?

414
00:41:23,458 --> 00:41:28,041
Yes, I just really want
to serve delicious coffee.

415
00:41:28,125 --> 00:41:30,583
Oh, I love projects like that.

416
00:41:31,250 --> 00:41:33,250
I know we'll do great. Leave it to me--

417
00:41:35,916 --> 00:41:36,875
Huh?

418
00:41:40,416 --> 00:41:41,333
Yusuke.

419
00:41:49,041 --> 00:41:52,666
I knew we'd meet again, Saeko.

420
00:42:00,541 --> 00:42:01,500
Do you remember

421
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:03,833
our promise?

422
00:42:07,375 --> 00:42:08,208
I remember.

423
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:12,000
Wait. How?

424
00:42:12,708 --> 00:42:14,708
Stuff like this really happens?

425
00:42:16,333 --> 00:42:18,333
I mean, I…

426
00:42:20,791 --> 00:42:22,375
regretted it so much.

427
00:42:22,916 --> 00:42:25,416
I left like it was nothing,
but I missed you.

428
00:42:26,750 --> 00:42:29,958
But I only knew your name!
I kept kicking myself.

429
00:42:33,250 --> 00:42:34,875
Don't laugh!

430
00:43:58,791 --> 00:44:00,291
Yusuke!

431
00:44:02,666 --> 00:44:06,958
This world is so boring
without you, Yusuke!

432
00:46:20,166 --> 00:46:21,000
Oh, sorry.

433
00:46:44,666 --> 00:46:46,666
To the one who reads this letter.

434
00:46:48,958 --> 00:46:52,750
The rules say I cannot share my name.

435
00:46:55,041 --> 00:47:00,750
I'm not sure how to put
my current feelings into words.

436
00:47:03,458 --> 00:47:07,125
All I can do is be grateful
for the life I've received

437
00:47:07,750 --> 00:47:09,083
and keep living on.

438
00:47:12,791 --> 00:47:14,041
And I pray

439
00:47:14,875 --> 00:47:18,041
that whoever is reading this letter

440
00:47:19,166 --> 00:47:21,375
will find happiness.

441
00:47:24,041 --> 00:47:25,833
If it's within my power,

442
00:47:27,041 --> 00:47:29,375
I would even like to come to your aid.

443
00:47:32,083 --> 00:47:34,083
I apologize for writing such things.

444
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:40,541
My heart can't help but feel this way.

445
00:51:14,875 --> 00:51:19,875
Subtitle translation by: Chul Woong Kim

